<subSubSection id="D354383CB3DFC3FF75C0AEC93415206F" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CCC7256411BF587872278BAD6AA98CC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5FD508D6BF6E1BB9D823CFDC832854B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
Name refers to the genus of the host plant 
<taxonomicName id="A15881D018705712918CDBC75B1B2E0D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Schima" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schima superba" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis id="1B940CF3CF9E516DA5D61CAF8B5693DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Schima superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B5302BAA80C29DBAD35197F1490422C" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="A7C97BB805BE1A2F55F9EB75D6469735" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C47BB3B4D11DCA7692D13E1506F6B765" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
Leaf spots irregular, pale brown in centre, brown to tan at margin. Sexual morph not observed. Asexual morph on PDA: Conidiomata solitary, scattered, black, raising above surface of culture medium, subglobose, exuding black conidial droplets from central ostioles after 10 days in light at 25 °C. Conidiophores cylindrical, hyaline, smooth-walled. Conidiogenous cells 9.0-16.5 
<normalizedToken id="090A5F9B048AA41036584FDDEB589EB3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-2.2 
<normalizedToken id="5C79FEEF954E59B17503975CEB872E61" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, phialidic, ampulliform, discrete, hyaline, smooth, thin-walled. Conidia 18-24 
<normalizedToken id="6E4E5F621308AEDFB1DB87290716D51D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6.0 
<normalizedToken id="46560FFBD0BBC62CB524E33C3F36E6BC" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, mean 
<normalizedToken id="A37B440DF66057EB67BB981AE2F630C2" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
SD = 20.5 
<normalizedToken id="4B60E79187CB7740B0784174B5D92E3B" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
1.1 
<normalizedToken id="DD688566A2F3D967BB998E11B2F0D929" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.5 
<normalizedToken id="AA9FBC4BD4A292898B44DB17F217BEEE" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.4 
<normalizedToken id="0950EBE079DBA17FB985D0F9803F8752" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, fusiform, tapering at both ends, 4-septate; apical cell 2.0-4.0 
<normalizedToken id="F834F711E3769272455904AC6EF5B003" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, conical, hyaline and smooth-walled; three median cells doliiform, 12.5-15.5 
<normalizedToken id="AA6F75A458CBF62B1DA89FE7FA8ED8BA" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, mean 
<normalizedToken id="C2EA72D225656A7ADE43DB89699E9E5C" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
SD = 14.2 
<normalizedToken id="9AB0E32C95187626DC42A77533A3ADC3" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.7 
<normalizedToken id="EB4D503320F9891E305633721020690A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, olivaceous, rough-walled, upper second cell 3.8-5.3 
<normalizedToken id="9B76D4571701080DE6FB2CE6CA6F3483" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, upper third cell 3.4-5.0 
<normalizedToken id="395B6651B56C6868DF886D7E1A1E42B1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, upper fourth cell 4.4-5.4 
<normalizedToken id="E3789F0B0A1F089F2C90870D4A9B80F5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long; basal cell 2.2-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="FDC89981E5919E1DF9221141307518C3" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, conical, hyaline and smooth-walled; apical appendage 7.0-12.5 
<normalizedToken id="16A84856D815C91C0FC5DDF6C58BD38C" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long (mean = 9.2 
<normalizedToken id="CBD4A10D7F7C9C9921474139C8D791AF" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), single, unbranched, central, tubular, filiform; basal appendage 2.5-5.0 
<normalizedToken id="553D4910626AAED5D2BD6A57E9CBEF2E" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, single, unbranched tubular, filiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B15472F5726FCCAA57269480F8A07BCD" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="22E8528EFE9ACA56A0C60303E7A3A40C" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5D63CD32A905F55548093A7C9F72CA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Colonies on PDA 39.0-45.0 mm in diameter after 15 days at 25 °C in darkness, growth rate 2.5-3.0 mm/day, irregularly circular, raised, dense surface with lobate edge, zonate in different sectors, light brown at the margin, brown at the centre; reverse brown at the margin, dark brown at the centre.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="654D2AAFD232D6BE643917D03CBA358D" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="additional specimen examined">
<paragraph id="F1B5B052D9344EB511166E7FF54647EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Additional specimen examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89BD07E5B3D9DE3615AAE716D62F0413" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
China, Hainan Province: East Harbour National Nature Reserve, 23 May 2021, Z.X. Zhang. On diseased leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="B6A549A1125F5C67F5BB76049F740254" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Schima" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schima superba" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis id="F53CAD381482F6086519D0A3ABD38335" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Schima superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, paratype HSAUP212202, living culture SAUCC212202; on diseased leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="6EBC40B29B6C4E8C11E2AA0531D7FA5D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Schima" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schima superba" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis id="4AFDF168C05316D5B893916F4DB8D57A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Schima superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, paratype HSAUP212203, living culture SAUCC212203.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DD1A567E172937D51FEEF526A59D5E64" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BCFE8EDBD2E6965C58873A361537E336" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC355ADD945503112341D915E0B41906" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="0D533F65D8E34A3008B6994AD285ACE6" authorityName="Z. X. Zhang, J. W. Xia &amp; X. G. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Monochaetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Monochaetia schimae" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="17147211124365F1157BCEEE0B4956DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Monochaetia schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is introduced based on the multi-locus phylogenetic analysis, with three isolates clustering separately in a well-supported clade (BI/ML = 0.99/96). 
<taxonomicName id="B8D79306735AE09BAE5D7914DE627091" authorityName="Z. X. Zhang, J. W. Xia &amp; X. G. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Monochaetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Monochaetia schimae" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="DEAAC7A645520F098A371F8D031990AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Monochaetia schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="CD072B7D46B2BEDD0095DDC6BD033F3C" genus="M." lsidName="M. castaneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="castaneae">
<emphasis id="1A763FC3054130257B3DA6AEEA2494E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. castaneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="C12BC64AD6A15252BEA9DFFF07FBD3A3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis id="34C5482DE43DCE6156EDE4BD088941BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="752CF58168BA936847D6FA0DF78E450A" genus="M." lsidName="M. ilicis" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis id="E4618FD6298318B50389A6A4462465B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="F55291FF8FB4D029A0A92B3C189BB7DE" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ilex" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5B0C6CD9A56FAC3A3B5398E4F538C5F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., and 
<taxonomicName id="38F5236252802167FDA8CBA13A1AFDA5" genus="M." lsidName="M. junipericola" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="junipericola">
<emphasis id="D80E31DCA3C64068EAA50F9E8BCDE561" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. junipericola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from twigs of 
<taxonomicName id="C5358DA6436662589514A7B88FD9B66B" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Juniperus communis" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="B6EE1A54492CC2AA7A965DF1B06D110D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Juniperus communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="EB4BA4D45E0C4A0CB275D4CEE9EAB9B2" authorityName="Z. X. Zhang, J. W. Xia &amp; X. G. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Monochaetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Monochaetia schimae" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="A30A22D35FEDF70AE79A7337AF8E1F4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Monochaetia schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="7D926B04639F0CAB1D0B9065F2D15B18" genus="M." lsidName="M. castaneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="castaneae">
<emphasis id="627578ACE660A0D1BF2336D3666B7F85" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. castaneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 148 nucleotides (11/463 in ITS, 89/743 in 
<emphasis id="D241B638D7AF138803E4BE78E4534A89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tub2</emphasis>
and 48/403 in 
<emphasis id="3CBDB62CC59CE8C6779BF5ECE7CBBBCD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tef1</emphasis>
), from 
<taxonomicName id="77E466ADE3ABB96E7F11E015849A63D5" genus="M." lsidName="M. ilicis" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis id="6AAA0F0E2C0B9F487628160B9B6CD17B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 94 nucleotides (18/526 in ITS, 32/698 in 
<emphasis id="2B36B1A39450E9BC039FF9B48A4636AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tub2</emphasis>
and 44/456 in 
<emphasis id="6CA579D2B0D0DA0942B8FB8D8DEE7C12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tef1</emphasis>
), and from 
<taxonomicName id="7C203F416F84424302D8C996D987C71B" genus="M." lsidName="M. junipericola" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="junipericola">
<emphasis id="0AB4222DF563043EB43E4E2E2A79E8DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. junipericola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 91 nucleotides (10/524 in ITS, 40/411 in 
<emphasis id="9292D0BA5256E3A3D835B59F9D8464EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tub2</emphasis>
and 41/304 in 
<emphasis id="2EBFBCEFBF47AA24D67C7ADC7D5CF468" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">tef1</emphasis>
). Furthermore, they are distinguished by hosts and conidial sizes (18.0-24.0 
<normalizedToken id="98BA050235D895456B4C637C5A5422E6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6.0 
<normalizedToken id="4EC20708B09E84D1B395ADBF1DFE1F90" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="D1D76A65AA84A5C4807B645C0D56DE3E" genus="M." lsidName="M. schimae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="273DB7AA827258EEA4AA4D4CDBEA15F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 18.8-27.3 
<normalizedToken id="CDAF5CFBFFF82DB939E197AC0FDFFFCD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.7-6.6 
<normalizedToken id="86442BB3876FD0A0B75F5C916431D0F9" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="5215EF8F14C42804BBB4CEA89621C0E9" genus="M." lsidName="M. castaneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="castaneae">
<emphasis id="CC41BEEAB8B9C0EBEDF6AAC86EAFD0F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. castaneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 20.0-27.0 
<normalizedToken id="197118EBD591F877C418D3365DC2E291" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.0-8.0 
<normalizedToken id="348C41589E553B50606DF2BB0AB1DA63" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="F55DA96512B65BC4D067D1777419404D" genus="M." lsidName="M. ilicis" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis id="0ADB4EF474F55F1C586300E214B28BC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 22.0-28.0 
<normalizedToken id="0E775CF81B33E2591C37BCC61F0AEFD9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.0-7.0 
<normalizedToken id="75773FC9682E5F83CCED2C366F4BDB09" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="CC2BFFD86574D878F9C69686924E2DDB" genus="M." lsidName="M. junipericola" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="junipericola">
<emphasis id="A33C5A20C999328D1A079F0989C03372" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. junipericola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In morphology, 
<taxonomicName id="ACC53CAA5A92A04A4A2BBBE60266DED7" authorityName="C.M.Tian &amp; N.Jiang" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Monochaetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Monochaetia castaneae" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="castaneae">
<emphasis id="74ABC1E3D3B90BFB747C2F89FB35E7B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Monochaetia castaneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="3538FEE65FA5EDDD92AC4C91FEC4D43C" genus="M." lsidName="M. schimae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="623DD605CF4DAD53EB3DB7D4D6EC50AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour of colonies (cinnamon vs. brown), 
<taxonomicName id="524E4F4E22D20B121FB869F849B4FB98" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Monochaetia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Monochaetia ilicis" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis id="1C9054D11884D236AEFF29D957256D80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Monochaetia ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CB8AD5CEC053B0C8CAAF2696699208F2" genus="M." lsidName="M. schimae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="50836C499A07A17ABE0806564B6E5BFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour of median cells (brown vs. olivaceous), and 
<taxonomicName id="5422AFF07D026F9BE07E118341F969AB" genus="M." lsidName="M. junipericola" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="junipericola">
<emphasis id="BAF23C56284607AE398F90289E90993E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. junipericola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A0F9684B8DE6A1AC5D37F30789E95061" genus="M." lsidName="M. schimae" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis id="A16F59FA49C27A99700F109F19783B42" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">M. schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer conidiogenous cells (10.0-30.0 
<normalizedToken id="DAA7B94E546E0595D55EA00D1FDE366A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
vs. 9.0-16.5 
<normalizedToken id="AD54F19FA4218DADFAE0DA475A044C51" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="2FFDD385EC55A5BC1CA8ACCDE31FA39D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.291.2.3" author="de Silva, N" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" pagination="123 - 132" refId="B12" refString="de Silva, N, Phookamsak, R, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Thambugala, KM, Jayarama Bhat, D, Al-Sadi, AM, Lumyong, S, Hyde, KD, 2017. Monochaetia ilexae sp. nov. (Pestalotiopsidaceae) from Yunnan Province in China. Phytotaxa 291 (2): 123 - 132, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.291.2.3" title="Monochaetia ilexae sp. nov. (Pestalotiopsidaceae) from Yunnan Province in China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.291.2.3" volume="291" year="2017">de Silva et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="03988EF66CB9655FFCAF3A289EF159D0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.08" author="Crous, PW" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" pagination="169 - 215" refId="B11" refString="Crous, PW, Schumacher, RK, Wingfield, MJ, Akulov, A, Denman, S, Roux, J, Braun, U, Burgess, T, Carnegie, AJ, Vaczy, KZ, Guatimosim, E, Schwartsburd, PB, Barreto, RW, Hernandez-Restrepo, M, Lombard, L, Groenewald, JZ, 2018. New and Interesting Fungi. 1. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1 (1): 169 - 215, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.08" title="New and Interesting Fungi. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.08" volume="1" year="2018">Crous et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
